      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i've heard some people saying these rules are basically just a way for the govt to force a green agenda even if it hurts the economy, but i also see people arguing that the long term environmental stability is worth the cost. how do these two sides actually clash when you look at the economic data? like, is there any real evidence that the benefits outweigh these costs for a small shop?",
