      "role": "user",
      "content": "wow, $100 billion is huge. that's pretty intense. but i'm curious though—some economists argue that there are 'positive externalities' like reduced healthcare costs from better air quality or even new jobs in the green tech sector that offset these initial losses. why do you think those arguments don't seem to get much weight compared to the compliance cost data you're seeing?",
